T1  - Single-equation estimators and aggregation restrictions when equations have the same sets of regressors
AU  - Denton, Frank T.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 8
IS  - 2
SP  - 173
EP  - 179
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/10/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(78)90026-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440767890026X
AB  - It is well known that linear equations subject to cross-equation aggregation restrictions can be ‘stacked’ and estimated simultaneously. However, if every equation contains the same set of regressors, a number of single-equation estimation procedures can be employed. The applicability of ordinary least squares is widely recognized but the article demonstrates that the class of applicable estimators is much broaders than OLS. Under specified conditions, the class includes instrumental variables, generalized least squares, ridge regression, two-stage least squares, k-class estimators, and indirect least squares. Transformations of the original equations and other related matters are discussed also.
ER  - 

